    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - IC BUS SERVICE MANUAL - BUS BODY CONSTRUCTION - BODY PANEL
        INSTALLATION PROCEDURE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>BODY PANEL INSTALLATION PROCEDURE</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the replacement panel with an overlap per section removed (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f4700132">Figure 30</hotlnk>). Position the panel in the same location as the original
                part.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Replacement panels are not pre-punched. Drilling may be required for rivet installation and
                    alignment.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f4700132" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/G4700132.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 30. Note Previous Overlap</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a #10 drill bit to ream out the rivet holes in the replacement panel (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f4700133">Figure 31</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f4700133" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/G4700133.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 31. Ream Out Holes</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use #12 screws to secure the panel in position until all holes are drilled for rivets.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install 3/16" HUCK MAGNA LOCK pop rivet.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Seal all overlapped joint seams with yellow sealer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f4700134">Figure 32</hotlnk>). Allow sealer to dry before painting.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Before repairing body construction, consult your local distributor for OEM parts and additional
                    information, if required. This procedure is only a general procedure for typical body side panel
                    repairs. Extreme care should be used in performing body repairs. The repair should only be done by
                    trained technicians.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f4700134" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/G4700134.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 32. Seal All Seams</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
